post_text:
Due to mandatory close contact quarantine requirements, there will be no Varsity Tiger football played on Friday, Sept 18 and Sept 25. Junior high games will still be played at their regularly scheduled times. Should these two varsity games be able to be made up, those dates will be announced. As of now, we plan to reschedule homecoming festivities on October 16th.

This is NOT due to a large number of sick students. We are implementing a mandatory quarantine due to "close contact" from a recent case from a high school student. We are doing everything we can to help decrease the spread of COVID-19. Thank you for your support and understanding!!!

Keri Winters
Superintendent, LKCISD

To Parents / Guardians of LKCISD Remote Learners:
We want to make you aware of an opportunity. Rather than waiting until after the first full 9-week grading period, we will be offering a chance for any virtual learners to return to onsite learning after Labor Day, this Tuesday, September 8.
We are proud of the efforts our students and staff have put into the return to school and can now say it has been a really smooth start; we want to encourage you to consider having your student come back to campus, join their classmates, and learn in person.
Please contact your child‚Äôs campus if you are interested in having them make the switch to onsite learning after Labor Day.

post_text:
Happy to report that we were spared from hurricane Laura! As I stayed home today, I was thinking we could've gone to school. However, I would rather get it wrong keeping students safe than to get it wrong taking a chance of getting stuck in a hurricane!!! Grateful it was mild for our community!

That being said, we will go back to school at regular time tomorrow!! Also, we will sell football tickets at the admin building from 8-2 tomorrow since we were closed on Thursday.

Remember to check temperatures and COVID symptoms before coming to school!!! Happy Friday!!

Keri Winters, Superintendent LKCISD

post_text:
Due to the threat of weather and widespread power outages related to Hurricane Laura, LKCISD will be closed on Thursday, August 27.

A decision regarding Friday, August 28 will not be made until later in the day on Thursday, as we want to wait and see the impact of the storm in our area.

All school events scheduled for Thursday are cancelled as well.

Please pray for our fellow Texans and our Louisiana neighbors who are along the coast and will be affected by Hurricane Laura!

Stay Safe Tigers!!!

Schedule Information for High School Students
At this time you will be able to view your schedule for the 2020-2021 school year by logging in to your parent portal account. You will also need to complete your online registration while in the parent portal program. If you need your portal id to create an account, please email Mrs. Stewart and she will help you set up your account.

Due to our current situation with COVID-19 and maintaining smaller class sizes for the 2020-2021 school year, schedule changes will be kept to a minimum. If you have questions or want to ask about a schedule change, you must do so by Tuesday, August 11th. Please email your questions to Mrs. Stewart at jstewart@lkcisd.net.

Online registration for the 2020-2021 school year is now open! You‚Äôll need to log in to your parent portal account and complete the registration process for each of your students. If you do not have a parent portal account, one will need to be created. Please contact lkhelpline@lkcisd.net with your name, your student‚Äôs name, and your student‚Äôs birthday to receive a portal ID and to place your email address on file with the school.

Please note that online registration is for returning students only. New students will need to contact lkhelpline@lkcisd.net to get information on registering.

If you need assistance with online registration, we will be offering assistance in-person BY APPOINTMENT ONLY on 2 Saturdays: July 18th and July 25th from 8AM to 6PM. These sessions will take place at our administration building. Only one person may attend these appointments and masks are encouraged, but not required. You can book an appointment by visiting the following link: https://lkregistration.youcanbook.me/

If you have any questions or concerns, please email lkhelpline@lkcisd.net.

post_text:
LKCISD parents and students,

I just wanted to send an update for the 20-21 school year. As of today, we still do not have clear direction from the state and the Texas Education Agency. School administrators and local area superintendents are meeting regularly and we are basically planning for all potential scenarios. As of now, the plan is to start school on August 13th. As far as rules and guidelines about HOW we do this they change weekly, but our doors will be open for you to send students to school. I know you need answers and I assure you we are working DAILY to make preparations. We have been told we should have answers soon. It is our priority to keep our community, students, and staff safe. Thank you for your patience and prayers!!

Until then, enjoy the rest of the summer and stay healthy!!

Sincerely,
Keri Winters
Superintendent, LKCISD

post_text: The time is almost upon us once again for registration for school! This year will be different from before as this year, we will be conducting ALL registration procedures online. Online registration will open in first week of July. We will be holding registration days on July 18th and July 25th. These will run from 10AM to 6PM. Computer labs will be available for parents to use in order to complete their children‚Äôs registration packets. School staff will be on hand to help with questions and concerns about parent portal accounts, how to register, etc. In addition, we will have several staff members on hand to complete your child‚Äôs registration in an interview type process. All you have to do is answer a series of questions, and we can perform the registration for you! You will need proper identification to take advantage of this type of registration. Look for more information coming soon! If you have any questions, comments or concerns in the meantime, email lkhelpline@lkcisd.net !

Per orders from the governor and commissioner of education, the only graduation ceremonies we can have before June 1 are virtual and drive thru. Our senior officers have voted to have an in-person graduation ceremony at Jack Hetherington Stadium on June 5 at 7:00 PM. There will be rules and restrictions placed as necessary. As of now, the law limits small groups to 5 people from the same household. If this changes, we will make adjustments as well. Thank you for your patience and we are looking forward to a Once-in-a-lifetime memorable event!!!

More Information on graduation ceremony guidelines can be found at: https://tea.texas.gov/sites/default/files/graduation_ceremonies_5.5.pdf

L-K CISD Family,
Just a reminder of our new schedule for the remainder of the school year starting this week. We will run our routes and deliver meals on Monday, Wednesday, and Friday. We will double up amounts on Monday and Wednesday to help with Tuesday and Thursday.
Also, we will shift our Instructional Deliveries and Pick-up to Wednesday‚Äôs instead of Tuesday‚Äôs.

We hate that we will not get to finish the school year together on campuses, but are grateful we still get to see you and connect with you from our buses.

Please watch for updates on the L-K CISD Facebook page. And if you have questions, remember our LKHelpline@lkcisd.net.

Be safe, and all our blessings.

L-K CISD

post_text:
Per Governor Abbott‚Äôs order today, LKCISD will not reopen for the 2019-2020 school year.

As of this time, we are still providing meals and remote instruction. Starting next week, we will deliver meals on Monday, Wednesday, and Friday only. On Mondays and Wednesdays, we will provide 2 breakfast and 2 lunches for each student. Wednesdays will be our days to deliver instructional packets. We will also have pick up on Wednesday from 1-3, or will be available to be downloaded from www.lkcisd.net.

Details regarding graduation, etc will be released once we receive more detailed guidance from the Texas Education Agency & State of Texas!

post_text:
Dear LKCISD families,

Happy Friday to what has been a very long week!!! I am happy to report that I have had no additional staff sick!!! I want to thank everyone that has filled out the survey. Please do so if you have not yet. Turns out, the majority of our people still want to pick up or have their work delivered. We are going to spend this week organizing the data we received and contacting those we haven't heard from. Because of this, there will be NO INSTRUCTIONAL MATERIALS dropped off or picked up this week. That gives you kids an extra week to do the work (DC kids, you better double check with your teachers - may not apply to you!!!).

The next available instructional packets will be Tuesday, April 14. They will available to be delivered, picked up, or downloaded off of our website. !

It is such a blessing to have staff willing to continuously serve our students. None of this would work without the commitment of our folks!! I hope you all have a safe and HEALTHY weekend!!

Sincerely,
Keri Winters
Superintendent, LKCISD

post_text:
Dear LK Families,

We would like for you to fill out this survey to let us know how you want you to receive your instructional materials. We will be sending out an FAQ regarding how these materials will be graded soon. Our primary objective is that our students can retain their instructional level they had when they left and these instructional packets will help with that. It is important for your child's future education that they continue to do school work during this time.

Please share this survey so we can reach as many families as possible. You only need to fill out one survey per household, just please include all kids names. This will also be posted on our school website for those that don't have Facebook. Your answers will be confidential and can only be seen by designated people in LKCISD.

Please send questions to LKHelpline@lkcisd.net.

https://forms.gle/fZ5oE6MqJ7FCtFLZ8

Kristen Kerr is with Nathan Trammell and 24 others.
March 22 at 10:35 PM ¬∑

To my ELA students and parents. I have created a google classroom where I will post the assignments that are going out for the week, and I uploaded a video of me reading the passage I sent home. This allows students to have a regular lesson like they would in the classroom. Students are not required to watch, but I know that the read and think through helps many of them with comprehension! Class code will be in the comments below for those it applies to. I am uploading the first reading tonight for when it goes home on the buses tomorrow.
I will work on calling everyone, but sometimes this works faster! Please share this with other parents of freshmen and sophomores and ask the kids to tell their classmates!

shared_text:
Patsy Griffin
March 21 at 2:41 PM ¬∑

I am so thankful for my Linden-Kildare Tiger family. You are amazing. I am blessed that God put me in a great place to work and be a part of this wonderful team. Thanks to the wonderful administration team that has making all the tough and ever changing decisions. Thanks to our academic and logistics teams for working so smoothly together. We are Better Together and we love our Linden-Kildare kids. We miss them so much. They are our reason for what we do. Our prayers go out to them and their families. In this new time of figuring out our new place and how to continue our lives, we need to remember to be kind. Let us care for each other and remember to always think of others. I pray for our families, our kids, our communities. May we all stay calm and take care of each other. God bless you all. Hugs to my kids.

post_text:
Governor Abbott just announced new statewide restrictions for people and businesses Thursday to help slow the spread of the coronavirus.

Abbott's executive order closes dine-in restaurants, bars, gyms across the State of Texas. Takeout/delivery will be allowed. All schools across the state are also closed. The order starts midnight tomorrow through April 3, although it could be extended.

This automatically extends our school closure through April 3.

Linden-Kildare Tiger Tracks Yearbook
March 18 at 12:48 AM ¬∑

Attention: Linden-Kildare Tiger Tracks Yearbook Staff, Check your school email. I have set up a private facebook group to aid in the communication, creative efforts and production of the 2020 Tiger Tracks Yearbook. If you are my fb friend I sent you an invite. If you are not my fb friend please have someone add you to the group or request to be my friend and I will add you. I have so missed you all and can't wait to hear from you. You are an amazing staff and I have full faith that together nothing can stop us. Let me know if there is anything you need. I am happy to help in whatever means necessary. Talk with you soon. Sincerely, Mrs. Siglinda Smoak

We are very excited to have Mr.Keith Deltano here with us in just 5 short days!! Parents, we want YOU to be apart of this great event!
Keith's presentations go beyond the bystander/bully/victim labels to get at the underlying causes of bullying. He challenges the youth and adults in the audience to seriously contemplate how they view one another.

Research has shown about 20% of students ages 12-18 experience bullying.

post_text:
Shout out to Kinley Harris for representing LK in such a grand way! Kinley has been successfully showing for 8 years. She has had a top 10 placing heifer at two Ft. Worth & Houston shows including a top 5 heifer in Ft. Worth, and a 4th place heifer in San Antonio. She has won Four States Fair Steer Show many years ago and just a few weeks ago had a 4th place heifer at Ft. Worth.

Last week at the Ft Worth steer show, Kinley's steer was 2nd in his class of 70 and a top 8 out of 240 steers. Congrats to Kinley for her successes!!!

Juniors & Seniors, please refer to the message below from Mrs. Griffin in regards to Prom and the Sadie Hawkins Dance.

* Juniors & Seniors that are attending prom this year will need to make sure their junior prom dues have been paid. They are due no later than February 20th. If their dues have not been paid or earned through fundraising then they will not be able to attend prom. If they are not sure, please see Mrs. Griffin.

* The Junior Class will host a " Sadie Hawkins Dance " on Saturday February 8th from 8:00 to 11:00 p.m. in the High School Cafeteria. Tickets are $5.00 each. If a student chooses to bring a date that is not a L-K high school student, they will need to fill out an Out of School Date Form. They are due back completed no later than Tuesday February 4th.
( Form attached)

post_text: Paul Wong visited the 2nd grade for Christmas Around the World. Students learned about the culture of Malaysia and how they celebrate. We thank him for sharing his time and culture with our students.

post_text: McLeod lost a teacher and student this weekend in a tragic car accident. If you feel compelled to donate some money to this sweet family, please bring it to the administration building this week and we will make sure it gets there. Life is short. LOVE BIG!!
shared_text:
McLeod ISD
October 14, 2019 at 5:06 PM ¬∑

We will be taking up a love offering for the Baig family. They have immediate expenses incurred being at the hospital with no notice. Plus, they are working on funeral arrangements and such. If you feel led to donate, you may bring money to the administration office. Mrs. May and Mrs. Lambeth will be going to see the family tomorrow and will take what we have at the time. But we will take up money as long as it comes in and make sure all of it gets to the family. Thank you for loving our community and school family. Our morning has been tough, but we have made it with all of the support. We have had parent and community volunteers with us. Area pastors were with us this morning and are still on call. Parents and McLeod Tabernacle have fed our staff today. Region * sent us some wonderful people to support our effort. The outreach from our community schools has been tremendous. We know we are loved and we are thankful in the storm.

post_text:
From early in the morning,
Until I go to sleep each day,
I know my grandparents love me,
In a very special way.

Sometimes it‚Äôs tea and crackers,
Sometimes a walk in the park,
Sometimes it‚Äôs just a hug when I‚Äôm scared and in the dark.

I love to hear their stories,
About the past and where they‚Äôre from,
And I know their hearts are filled for me,
With never-ending love.

Happy Grandparents Day!!!

post_text:
Last night our JV team hosted a Freshman team from Texas High.
We came out victorious by the score of 30-0. The night got started quickly with a long kickoff return from Dekotah Kenward. Two plays later Jay Birmingham scored a touchdown. After a defensive stop Russell Nance returned a punt 45 yards for a touchdown. Jay Birmingham converted the 2 point play. After another defensive stop, Dekotah Kenward had a touchdown run and Michael Lane converted the 2 point play. Jay Birmingham added another touchdown and 2 point conversion to round out the scoring. Defensively Jordan Swanson and Kyler Fitts had multiple sacks of the quarterback. Clayton Mulkey and Averie Fisher had multiple tackles for loss. AJ Price and Carter Foreman both broke up pass completions and Jay Birmingham had an interception. Rolle Patterson and Taeshaun Mithcell played well on both sides of the ball. It was a team effort by the Tigers with everyone doing their part. We will play at home again next week against DeKalb. Thank you for your support.
Coach John Roberts

FYI: YEARBOOK PICTURES ARE NEXT WEEK

Elementary School = Thursday, Sept 5th

Seniors will take theirs on Wednesday, Sept. 25th
shared_text:
Linden-Kildare Tiger Tracks Yearbook
August 29, 2019 at 5:20 PM ¬∑

Yearbook Pictures are next week. The High School and Junior High will be on Wednesday, Sept. 4th and the Elementary School will be on next Thursday, Sept. 5th. Picture package forms should be coming home soon with your child. If you do not receive a form please feel free to either print out this form or send payment in an envelope with your students name, grade and picture package noted on the outside of envelope. Thank you, Siglinda Smoak, Linden-Kildare Tiger Tracks Yearbooks Adviser 903-657-4846

post_text:
We are looking forward to the Linden Kildare High School blood drive on 09/09/2019, 08:00 AM to 03:00 PM. Meeting the goal of 39 donations is vital as hospitals are counting on it.

You may schedule blood drive appointments here https://donor.lifeshare.org/donor/schedules/drive_schedule/198699 and forward this link to others to schedule their own appointments. Would you please convey this information to all possible donors?

The community blood supply would not be possible without volunteer blood drive organizers like you. Thank you for taking on this cause to help so many others!

2019 Lady Tiger Volleyball Fundraiser
